==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amyl nitrite
<hw>Amyl nitrite</hw>. <def>A yellowish oily volatile liquid,
<chform>C5H11NO2</chform>, used in medicine as a heart stimulant and a
vasodilator. The inhalation of its vapor instantly produces flushing of
the face.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amylobacter</ent>⟦br⟧
